    <p>Two things: (1) your completed water budget sheet — inputs, storage change, outputs, all numbers shown · (2) a 2-sentence claim — sentence one names the classification (deficit, balance, surplus) <em>with the period</em> ("for the monsoon month of October" or "for the full year"). Sentence two names one specific factor that would change the classification ("if dry-season groundwater pumping were halved, the basin would shift from deficit to balance"). Generic ("water shortage," "more rain") doesn't clear the bar; specific is the move.</p>
